[3] Hong Kong Ex Cambodia
Date: 20 Jul 2006
From: Thomas Roesel <roesel@lycos.com>
Source: Hong Kong Centre for Health Protection [edited]
<http://www.chp.gov.hk/view_content.asp?lang=en&info_id=7200>

The Centre for Health Protection (CHP) of the Department of Health
confirmed an imported case of dengue fever today [19 Jul 2006] and
urged people to guard against the disease.
Case details are as follow:
Age: 40
Sex: Female
District of Residence: Kwai Chung
Date of Onset: 1 Jul 2006
Symptoms: Fever, diarrhea and skin rash.
Present Condition: Admitted to Pamela Youde Nethersole Eastern
Hospital on 10 Jul 2006. Already recovered and discharged on 15 Jul 2006.
Travel History: The patient works in Cambodia and returned to Hong
Kong on 10 Jul 2006.
Other: One travel collateral does not have any symptoms.
Cumulative Total in 2006: 17
* imported: 17
* local: 0
It is essential that people stay alert to the threat of dengue fever
and help in the reduction of mosquito breeding [sites].
--
