[8] Brazil - Rio
Date: 18 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-PORT <Promed-Port@promedmail.org>
Source: A Tarde, 17 Jul 2006 [Trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.google.com/u/atarde?q=dengue&tipo_busca=1&c=0&t=0&dex=&dx=&ds=&hl=pt&domains=atarde.com.br&sitesearch=atarde.com.br>

Over 26 000 cases of dengue have been registered in Rio, but the
Secretariat [of Health] said that the situation was under control.
The State Secretary of Health affirmed today [17 Jul 2006] that Rio
was not living through a dengue epidemic. The Secretary indicated
that the total number of dengue cases reached 26 712, a number 10
times greater than the 2580 dengue cases registered last year [2005].
Of this total [this year? - Mod.TY], 36 were [dengue] hemorrhagic
fever, and more seriously, with 5 deaths. This number does not
include the death of a DHF case in the municipality of Mage, in
Baixada Fluminense, who died this Sunday [16 Jul 2006?], advised the Secretary.
The municipalities most affected are Rio de Janeiro, where there were
12 255 cases with 3 deaths, followed by Angra dos Reis and Parati,
both on the south coast.
--
